						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the south verandah of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra,</hi> Tiruvīraṭṭānēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 14: 985 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 144 sheep by Mīṉavaṉ Vallavarayaṉ of [Pu]viḷa-nāḍu for burning one and half perpetual lamps in the temple of Tiruvīraṭṭānam-uḍaiyār at Tiruvadigai.</p>						

